</section>

<!-- ═══ REAL ENGLISH ═══ -->

<section id="real">
  <div class="sec-label">
    <div class="sec-num">💡</div>
    <div class="sec-tag">Real English</div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h2>🍗 "Have" também significa comer, beber e tomar!</h2>
    <div class="obs">
      📌 <strong>OBS:</strong> Usamos <em>have</em> também no lugar de comer ou beber!<br/>
      <em>ex: I have chicken for lunch. / I have coffee in the morning.</em>
    </div>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table class="vtable">
        <thead><tr><th>Situação</th><th>Exemplo</th><th>Tradução</th><th>Ouvir</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>☕ Tomar bebida</td><td>I have coffee every morning.</td><td>Tomo café toda manhã.</td><td><button class="speak-btn" onclick="speak('I have coffee every morning.')">🔊</button></td></tr>
          <tr><td>🥗 Comer refeição</td><td>I have chicken for lunch.</td><td>Como frango no almoço.</td><td><button class="speak-btn" onclick="speak('I have chicken for lunch.')">🔊</button></td></tr>
          <tr><td>🥛 Beber algo</td><td>I have juice in the afternoon.</td><td>Bebo suco à tarde.</td><td><button class="speak-btn" onclick="speak('I have juice in the afternoon.')">🔊</button></td></tr>
          <tr><td>🍽️ Jantar</td><td>We have dinner at 7pm.</td><td>Jantamos às 19h.</td><td><button class="speak-btn" onclick="speak('We have dinner at 7pm.')">🔊</button></td></tr>
          <tr><td>🍳 Café da manhã</td><td>She has breakfast early.</td><td>Ela toma café cedo.</td><td><button class="speak-btn" onclick="speak('She has breakfast early.')">🔊</button></td></tr>
          <tr><td>🧃 Lanche</td><td>They have a snack at school.</td><td>Eles lancham na escola.</td><td><button class="speak-btn" onclick="speak('They have a snack at school.')">🔊</button></td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h2>👤 Possessive Adjectives — His & Her</h2>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table class="vtable">
        <thead><tr><th>Pronome</th><th>Tradução</th><th>Exemplo</th><th>Ouvir</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><strong>His</strong></td><td>dele</td><td>This is his house.</td><td><button class="speak-btn" onclick="speak('This is his house.')">🔊</button></td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Her</strong></td><td>dela</td><td>Ana is her mother.</td><td><button class="speak-btn" onclick="speak('Ana is her mother.')">🔊</button></td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h2>🎙️ Pronunciation Tip — Sons finais em -er e -or</h2>
    <div class="pron">
      🔊 <strong>Dica EasyWay:</strong> O <strong>-er</strong> no final <em>não</em> soa como "ÉR" forte.<br/>
      O som é fraco e relaxado: <strong>muh-ther</strong>, <strong>sis-ter</strong>.<br/>
      Pratique clicando nas palavras abaixo! 👇
    </div>
    <div class="pron-grid">
      <div class="pron-card" onclick="speak('mother')"><div class="word">mother</div><div class="phonetic">/ ˈmʌð.ər /</div></div>
      <div class="pron-card" onclick="speak('father')"><div class="word">father</div><div class="phonetic">/ ˈfɑː.ðər /</div></div>
      <div class="pron-card" onclick="speak('sister')"><div class="word">sister</div><div class="phonetic">/ ˈsɪs.tər /</div></div>
      <div class="pron-card" onclick="speak('brother')"><div class="word">brother</div><div class="phonetic">/ ˈbrʌð.ər /</div></div>
      <div class="pron-card" onclick="speak('teacher')"><div class="word">teacher</div><div class="phonetic">/ ˈtiː.tʃər /</div></div>
      <div class="pron-card" onclick="speak('daughter')"><div class="word">daughter</div><div class="phonetic">/ ˈdɔː.tər /</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

